Solar panels are typically arranged in systems, arrays, that include an inverter to convert DC to alternating current (AC) for household use, and sometimes controllers, meters and trackers.  Installing solar panels on rooftops solar or in solar farms helps supply clean energy to the electricity grid.  Some advantages of solar panels are that they use a renewable and clean source of energy, reduce greenhouse gas emissions, and lower electricity bills.  Despite their initial high costs, advancements in technology have made solar panels more efficient and accessible for residential, commercial, and industrial use.  Solar panels are also crucial in space missions, providing a reliable energy source.  Embrace solar energy for a sustainable future and signifiant long-term savings !
